summary: This is an email chain from September 2021 regarding the transfer of discovery materials, specifically communications between an FBI Special Agent and victim/witness/attorneys, in the Ghislaine Maxwell case. The emails discuss technical issues with file formats and the use of the USAfx system for secure transfer.

persons.name: Special Agent FBI New York Field Office Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk
persons.context: The FBI Special Agent is the sender of the initial email attaching discovery communications with victim/witness/attorneys and is coordinating the file transfer with the prosecution team.

events.title: Discovery Communications Transfer Initiated
events.description: An FBI Special Agent sends a zip file containing communications with victim/witness/attorneys to the prosecution team as part of discovery in the Ghislaine Maxwell case.
personsInvolved: Special Agent FBI New York Field Office Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk

events.title: File Transfer Issues and Re-upload
events.description: The prosecution team reports the zip file is unopenable; the FBI Special Agent re-uploads the communications unzipped to the USAfx system in a folder designated for Agent Communications for the Maxwell case (3500).
personsInvolved: Special Agent FBI New York Field Office Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk

keyFacts: The document is part of discovery in United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (referenced as '3500 (Maxwell)').
The communications being transferred are between an FBI Special Agent and victim/witness/attorneys.
The file transfer uses the USAfx system, a secure platform for sharing sensitive legal materials.
The FBI Special Agent works on the Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking Desk at the New York Field Office.
The email chain highlights procedural coordination between law enforcement and prosecutors in a high-profile case.
